Keep it: Commit it if it's a global setting you want everywhere.

Isolate it: Move that junk to ~/.bashrc.local (which isn't tracked by Git) to keep your "pure" config clean.

The Verdict
Yes, use Stow. It’s lightweight, it’s standard, and it doesn't require you to learn some bloated "dotfile manager" framework that will be abandoned in six months.

