The Amateur Way: You hardcode export STRIPE_API_KEY="sk_test_..." in your ~/.bashrc. Now every script on your computer has access to your keys. Brilliant.

The Tedious Way: You keep a .env file and manually run source .env every time you cd into a project. You’ll forget to do this exactly when it matters most.

How It Works (The .envrc File)
direnv looks for a file called .envrc in your current directory. When you cd into that folder, it loads those variables. When you cd out, it unloads them. It’s like magic, but with more logic.

1. Installation & The "Thunder" Update
First, install it: sudo pacman -S direnv.
