cd ~/projects/secret-app

Create the file: echo "export API_KEY=12345" > .envrc

The Security Check: direnv will scream at you that the file isn't authorized (to prevent malicious folders from hijacking your shell). Run:
direnv allow

Now, whenever you enter that folder, API_KEY is set. When you cd .., it vanishes.

3. The "Pro" Use Case: Python Virtual Envs
If you’re tired of typing source venv/bin/activate like a peasant, put this in your .envrc:

Bash
layout python python3
Now, the moment you cd into your project, your Python virtual environment is activated automatically.

