Because we spent all that time setting up a clean, synced dotfile repo, right?

Your Dotfiles: Contain your global logic (the eval hook).

Your Projects: Contain the .envrc (which you should usually .gitignore so your keys don't end up on GitHub).

The Verdict
direnv is the final piece of the puzzle. It keeps your global environment "pure" and your project-specific junk exactly where it belongs: in the project folder.

